[There is very limited information given in the news report above describing the outbreak in an isolated village in Uttarkashi in northern India that is affecting more than 50 mainly teenage girls who complained of throat pain complicated by kidney disease. We are not told how they know that the kidneys were involved. This clinical pattern suggests post-streptococcal glomerulonephritis following group A streptococcal pharyngitis. More information would be appreciated on this outbreak from knowledgeable sources.

Uttarkashi is a town and district in the mountainous state of Uttarakhand in northern India bordering the Tibet Autonomous Region of China to the north. Uttarkashi is home to a number of ashrams, many Hindu temples and pilgrimage centers, and also to the Nehru Institute of Mountaineering (https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Uttarkashi). - Mod.ML

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=4431745,321.]
